Treasures of the British Museum
Viking Press | 1972 | ISBN: 0670726567 | English | 232 pages | PDF | 24 MB

The British Museum houses and displays one of the largest and finest permanent exhibitions in the world. It is visited by over two million people every year, from school children to specialists in almost any subject one could mention. The purpose of this book is to introduce the reader to the Museum and to the fascinating objects that are to be found in its various departments.
